<DocsLayout title="Tips & Tricks" section="Helpful Resources">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Maximize efficiency in Field Promax with these tips and tricks. Learn how to use
    search features, group data, work with editable PDF forms, and set up default products.
  </p>

  <h2>Search Box</h2>
  <img src="/images/helpful-resources/tipsandtricks_02.png" alt="Search Box" />
  <p>
    Use the Search box in the top left to quickly find customers or work orders.
    From the search results, you can perform numerous actions directly.
  </p>

  <h2>Advanced Search</h2>
  <img src="/images/helpful-resources/tipsandtricks_01.png" alt="Advanced Search" />
  <p>
    Find a needle in a haystack by searching for work orders, estimates, or customers
    using keywords:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Click the magnifying glass in the top right</li>
    <li>Define your search criteria</li>
    <li>Example: Find all work orders with "faucet" in the description</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Group Column Data</h2>
  <img src="/images/helpful-resources/tipsandtricks_03.webp" alt="Group Columns" />
  <p>Customize how you view lists in Field Promax:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Quickly group columns by dragging headers to the grouping bar</li>
    <li>Move and resize columns to your preference</li>
    <li>Example: In Open Work Orders, select "All" items per page, then drag "Job Type" to the grouping bar to organize by job type</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Mobile Editable PDF Forms</h2>
  <img src="/images/helpful-resources/tipsandtricks_04.webp" alt="Editable PDF" />
  <p>
    Attach editable PDF forms for technicians to complete in the field. Useful when
    specific forms need to be filled out during work.
  </p>
  <h3>How to Use</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Download the <strong>Xodo PDF Reader & Scanner</strong> app (Google Play or App Store)</li>
    <li>Set Chrome or Safari as your default browser</li>
    <li>Download the attached editable PDF from the mobile app</li>
    <li>Open with XODO, make changes, and save</li>
    <li>Upload the completed PDF to the Documents section of the work order</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Default Products</h2>
  <img src="/images/helpful-resources/tipsandtricks_05.webp" alt="Default Products" />
  <p>
    Automatically add products when work orders are created:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Manage Lists</strong> → <strong>Job Types and Checklist</strong></li>
    <li>Create or edit a Job Type</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Attach Default Products</strong></li>
    <li>When work orders are created with this Job Type, products are added automatically</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Notifications & Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Ensure your user permissions allow access to these features</li>
    <li>Some features require Administrator access to configure</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips Summary</h2>
  <div class="callout callout-tip">
    <p>
      <strong>Use the search box</strong> to find what you need quickly.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Use advanced search</strong> for specific work orders, estimates, or customers.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Group column data</strong> to view information in different ways.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Use mobile editable PDFs</strong> to save time during work.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Add default products</strong> to speed up work order creation.
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
